CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 27, 1962, pg. 14, reads: "The Gays - Members of the Pittsburgh chapter of Gay Notheasterners, popularly called 'The Gays,' are pictured at the home of the Russell Sheltons where they hosted a champagne sip last Sunday. Seated from left: Mmes. Russell Shelton, hostess; Edward H. Hale and Robert T. McEnheimer. Standing (second row): Mmes. pg. L. Prattis, president; Robert Woodruff, Julia Gaines, Max Johnson, William Allen, Miriam Bush, J. D. Lewis Sr. Top row: Mmes. Henry R. Smith Jr., W. P. Young, George Little, William Session, Earl Simms and Richard Jones. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Members of the Gay Northeasterners, seated from left: Jayne Shelton, Mrs. Hale, Mrs. McEnheimer; second row: Mrs. Prattis, Alyce Woodruff, Julia Gaines, Mrs. Johnson, Mrs. Allen, Miriam Bush, Mrs. Lewis; top row: Mrs. Smith, Mrs. Young, Mrs. Little, Mrs. Session, Mrs. Simms, and Mrs. Jones, posed on stairs in domestic interior, another version
